{
  "title": [
    "abs.pd~"
  ],
  "description": "simple wrapper for pd~ subprocess",
  "origin": "ELSE",
  "categories": [
    "Audio I/O",
    "Data Management"
  ],
  "inlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "signal",
          "description": "the left input to pd~ subprocess"
        },
        {
          "type": "anything",
          "description": "messages to the subprocess"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "signal",
          "description": "the right input to pd~ subprocess"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "outlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "signal",
          "description": "the left output from subprocess"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "signal",
          "description": "the right output from subprocess"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "arguments": [
    {
      "type": "symbol",
      "description": "pd file to load",
      "default": "none"
    }
  ],
  "flags": [],
  "methods": [
    {
      "type": "start <symbol>",
      "description": "start a subprocess, no symbol restarts last one"
    },
    {
      "type": "stop",
      "description": "stop the subprocess"
    },
    {
      "type": "show",
      "description": "open pd window"
    }
  ],
  "body": "[abs.pd~] loads a pd file into a subprocess via [pd~] and makes things more convenient like making the subprocess able to receive MIDI data from MIDI devices connected to the parent process (thanks to [sendmidi]). Also, you can open the subprocess patch by clicking on the object."
}